01:26.590 --> 01:27.864
Oh, shit.

01:31.350 --> 01:33.864
- Morning.
- You gotta be kidding me.

01:34.070 --> 01:35.708
Welcome home.

01:36.430 --> 01:38.819
- You don't look so good.
- I'm not talking to you.

01:40.110 --> 01:42.101
It's a social call.

01:44.590 --> 01:47.707
You're lucky,
having a friend like Mr. Hovis.

01:49.430 --> 01:52.740
Smithland Hovis?
The good buddy who posted your bail?

01:53.430 --> 01:54.783
- Smitty.
- It's funny.

01:54.990 --> 01:57.823
- He doesn't remember you that well.
- Just get out, man.

01:58.750 --> 02:02.345
You know, when I find out how Vic
and the other two got that bail money...

02:02.550 --> 02:06.589
...they're gonna wish that they had
a friend like your friend Smitty.

02:12.910 --> 02:14.389
Jesus.

02:15.070 --> 02:16.549
Is that blood?

02:18.750 --> 02:22.743
- Do you need a doctor?
- Just get the hell out! Just get out!

02:30.830 --> 02:35.699
Heard you had a rough week, so I told
Jon I'd stop by and check in on you.

02:37.150 --> 02:40.540
Sun will rise in the west the day
that man cares whether I live or die.

02:40.750 --> 02:43.469
Well, he did the same thing for me
with my ex.

02:44.750 --> 02:49.301
Did more for her than he did for me.
Sounds like you guys are close.

02:50.110 --> 02:53.989
We've been spending a lot of time
together actually on account of the job.

02:54.190 --> 02:57.978
But Jon's kind of tough to figure out.

02:58.190 --> 03:01.660
You know,
IAD cops are a different kind of breed.

03:01.870 --> 03:04.065
Consider yourself fortunate.

03:04.350 --> 03:07.467
He didn't tell me. You have kids?

03:07.670 --> 03:10.309
Family wasn't on Jon's to-do list.

03:10.510 --> 03:12.865
Just as well. Easier to move on.
You want coffee?

03:13.470 --> 03:15.222
Water's fine.

03:19.550 --> 03:21.620
So how does it work, you and the ex?

03:21.830 --> 03:25.505
Good and bad. But I look out for her,
make sure she gets what she needs.

03:26.630 --> 03:29.190
At least you guys have a connection.

03:29.830 --> 03:33.425
For better or worse.
You're not what I expected.

03:33.630 --> 03:36.940
Truth is, I didn't have a clue what sort
of woman Jon would have married.

03:37.150 --> 03:40.108
Neither did he. Still doesn't.

03:40.310 --> 03:42.221
Just like him
to send somebody else over...

03:42.430 --> 03:45.149
...to carry my emotional baggage.

03:46.630 --> 03:50.305
- Tell the prick I'm great.
- Hey, it's tough to be a cop's wife.

03:50.510 --> 03:52.899
Jon's wife is the job.

03:53.110 --> 03:54.589
What keeps him warm at night.

03:55.350 --> 03:58.467
And he's a coward
for not coming himself.

04:00.310 --> 04:03.427
Is there some other message
you'd like me to give him?

04:04.910 --> 04:06.389
Sure.

04:08.750 --> 04:10.581
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

04:11.550 --> 04:13.427
What about Jon?

04:13.630 --> 04:17.065
When Jon left me,
he made his choice.

04:17.269 --> 04:19.147
I'll make mine.

04:42.390 --> 04:46.303
- Hey. Where you been?
- I had an ex-wife thing.

04:46.990 --> 04:50.699
- What did you need us here for?
- Not her, me.

04:52.390 --> 04:54.346
I'm gonna take a deal. Just listen.

04:54.550 --> 04:58.748
If I plead guilty to the heroin thing,
this all seals off.

04:58.950 --> 05:00.861
Without me,
Kavanaugh's got nothing else.

05:01.070 --> 05:03.982
- He's got nothing on you guys.
- We're not feeding you to Antwon.

05:04.190 --> 05:05.384
Lompoc's an idle threat.

05:05.590 --> 05:08.058
The judge will place him
in a medium-security facility.

05:08.270 --> 05:10.784
Kavanaugh's not gonna let you escape
with some cush deal.

05:10.990 --> 05:13.185
He's got Emolia's testimony, man.
He wants years.

05:13.390 --> 05:15.426
- He's got the brass behind him.
- Not anymore.

05:15.630 --> 05:18.702
OIG and the chief are losing confidence
in Kavanaugh's investigation.

05:18.910 --> 05:19.865
DA's receptive.

05:20.070 --> 05:22.459
I plead guilty to theft
under colour of authority...

05:22.670 --> 05:24.581
...they'll drop the intent to distribute.

05:24.790 --> 05:28.226
- No.
- Five years. Up for parole in 18 months.

05:28.430 --> 05:29.943
Yeah.

05:30.150 --> 05:34.268
Man, you plead guilty,
it's your badge, it's your pension.

05:35.230 --> 05:37.949
We're talking prison.
Eighteen months isn't a week.

05:38.470 --> 05:39.949
I know.

05:40.550 --> 05:43.860
Don't do it. Don't do it, man.
We're fighting this, man.

05:44.070 --> 05:48.621
I don't wanna fight anymore.
I don't wanna fight anymore.

05:49.150 --> 05:52.904
All right, if you were in my place,
you'd take the hit.

05:53.110 --> 05:56.420
To protect me, the team.

05:58.590 --> 06:00.421
I know you would.

06:14.430 --> 06:17.786
No matter what, end of the day,
Kavanaugh's still got a brick of tar.

06:17.990 --> 06:20.299
- He's still got Emolia's word.
- You heard Becca.

06:20.510 --> 06:22.865
The chief's losing faith.
I'm discrediting this guy.

06:23.070 --> 06:26.665
So IAD brings in someone else.
They still have the same brick.

06:26.870 --> 06:29.703
I'm doing time no matter what.
This way I got some control.

06:29.910 --> 06:32.583
Look, I'm just so tired of not knowing
what's gonna happen.

06:32.790 --> 06:34.667
Worrying about the rest of you.

06:34.870 --> 06:36.588
I gotta see an end.

06:37.710 --> 06:41.862
- Jesus Christ, man.
- I gotta get back inside, talk to Becca.

06:42.790 --> 06:46.021
- Let us know if anything breaks.
- All right.

06:47.590 --> 06:50.741
For him to get out in 18 months,
he's gonna have to be a model inmate.

06:50.950 --> 06:52.383
That's not gonna happen.

06:52.590 --> 06:54.387
Protective custody's a joke.

06:54.590 --> 06:57.502
He's gonna be fighting for his life
the full five years.

06:57.710 --> 06:58.779
The hell is he thinking?

06:58.990 --> 07:02.141
Between Kavanaugh spinning doom
and Becca selling him a rose garden...

07:02.350 --> 07:04.705
...the poor guy doesn't know
what end is up.

07:04.990 --> 07:07.424
Or he's taking the deal
because he knows eventually...

07:07.630 --> 07:09.905
...Kavanaugh's gonna get him
to crack.

07:12.070 --> 07:13.344
I'm off to Lompoc.

07:22.030 --> 07:25.022
I was beginning to think that
you didn't have love for me anymore.

07:25.230 --> 07:29.143
I was getting a little jealous,
you spending time with another cop.

07:29.350 --> 07:31.910
Yeah, Kavanaugh's an intense cat,
isn't he?

07:32.110 --> 07:33.987
Hey, shame about Lemansky, man.

07:34.190 --> 07:37.466
But you do know that blondie
will end up in my backyard.

07:37.670 --> 07:39.979
We don't know anything yet.

07:40.310 --> 07:43.108
And if Lem does do time,
he's not gonna land here.

07:43.310 --> 07:45.460
I've got a real big backyard.

07:45.670 --> 07:50.061
And wherever he lands,
I decide his quality of life.

07:52.550 --> 07:56.782
- But that's why you're here.
- You need something, same as I do.

07:56.990 --> 08:00.141
Otherwise, you wouldn't have sent
that little black breezy to find me.

08:00.350 --> 08:04.423
Truth is, Antwon Mitchell's
the answer to all your prayers.

08:04.630 --> 08:07.622
Lemansky's guardian angel.

08:07.830 --> 08:10.788
See, we have a relationship,
you and me.

08:11.430 --> 08:13.546
That relationship's
had its ups and downs...

08:13.750 --> 08:16.503
...but it's still a relationship.
- You make me drive here...

08:16.710 --> 08:19.622
...for couples counselling,
or you got something to say?

08:21.790 --> 08:27.899
The Niners have taken a serious hit
since my incarceration.

08:28.390 --> 08:30.540
Halpern's been running them
under the radar.

08:30.750 --> 08:33.183
Until this black-brown shit storm
plays itself out.

08:33.390 --> 08:36.666
Look, that cranky black bitch
is afraid of his own goddamn shadow.

08:36.870 --> 08:39.429
I've got some serious
old-school weight coming in.

08:39.630 --> 08:41.461
Kern Little.

08:43.669 --> 08:46.309
I knew Kern's rap career
was in the dollar bin.

08:46.510 --> 08:50.788
- I didn't know he was back in colours.
- Eventually, they all come home.

08:51.110 --> 08:56.264
And Kern? He's eager to help me
with my cash-flow problem.

08:56.950 --> 08:59.623
I've gotta hand out a lot of turkeys
at Thanksgiving.

09:01.190 --> 09:03.658
There's a warehouse on Ridge Road.

09:04.270 --> 09:07.819
Place where they're storing
what's left of the seized assets.

09:09.630 --> 09:13.908
You want me
to rip off a P.D. Warehouse?

09:14.110 --> 09:15.782
Of course not.

09:15.990 --> 09:18.458
Kern's already put together
a team for that.

09:18.670 --> 09:23.425
You just gotta come up with a plan
on how and when to get my guys in.

09:23.630 --> 09:25.985
Walk Kern and his second, Moses,
through it.

09:26.190 --> 09:29.341
That's more than an escort.
That's a hooker and a hand job.

09:29.550 --> 09:34.146
Hey, that's the price for my guarantee
that Lemansky stays alive.

09:37.390 --> 09:39.381
Stand back. Nothing to see here.

09:39.590 --> 09:42.468
Jesus, his dick's gone.
Somebody find it.

09:43.390 --> 09:45.267
Detectives, another glory hole.

09:45.470 --> 09:48.507
- A jogger called it in. No ID.
- Gunshot?

09:48.710 --> 09:49.665
- Shit.
- No.

09:51.070 --> 09:52.981
There's a rat trap in one of the stalls.

09:53.190 --> 09:55.579
I was real careful
not to disturb the crime scene.

09:55.790 --> 09:58.782
Good thinking. Get that on ice,
send it with him to the hospital.

09:58.990 --> 10:01.902
It's not gonna matter if we don't
get him stable. We need to move.

10:02.110 --> 10:03.338
Let's get a canvass going.

10:03.550 --> 10:06.269
This is the same m.o.
As that attack couple of weeks ago.

10:06.470 --> 10:08.461
Suspect was male,
Caucasian, thirties.

10:08.670 --> 10:10.308
Well, let's not rule anyone out yet.

10:10.510 --> 10:13.070
In a world of men,
thought has even crossed my mind.

10:13.270 --> 10:15.864
Serrated teeth.
Interlocking, no less.

10:16.070 --> 10:18.538
This is more gothic
than the last glory-hole attack.

10:18.750 --> 10:20.945
- You talk to the hospital?
- Victim's unconscious.

10:21.150 --> 10:24.187
He sustained a head injury when he
passed out. He's in rough shape.

10:24.390 --> 10:27.541
So we have no way of knowing if
and when he'll be able to communicate.

10:27.750 --> 10:29.661
- Canvass turn up anything?
- Nothing so far.

10:29.870 --> 10:32.668
So we got dick. Which is more
than I can say for the victim.

10:32.870 --> 10:36.704
We need to get the word out.
Bookstores, bathhouses, bars...

10:36.910 --> 10:39.549
...anywhere this sort of activity
goes on.

10:39.750 --> 10:43.106
We need to re-interview the victim
in the first attack. What was his name?

10:43.310 --> 10:46.143
- He gave us everything he had.
- He never talked to a detective.

10:46.350 --> 10:49.069
It's Alarico Trujillo.
I'll write his address down.

10:49.270 --> 10:50.988
This Trujillo guy. He's married, kids.

10:51.190 --> 10:54.660
I told him I'd keep his name out of it
if he cooperated. He held up his end.

10:54.870 --> 10:56.906
This has escalated
way beyond a twisted prank.

10:57.110 --> 10:59.101
He's our only conscious witness.

10:59.310 --> 11:02.507
- We'll be discreet. Thank you.
- Okay.

11:07.550 --> 11:09.905
Is this thing even remotely safe?

11:10.110 --> 11:12.305
Make sure it is,
because we got no choice.

11:12.510 --> 11:15.468
- Antwon's the devil we know.
- Yeah, what if it's the other devil?

11:15.670 --> 11:16.785
Kavanaugh laying a trap?

11:16.990 --> 11:19.948
He's been cutting deals with Antwon,
maybe this is his last stab.

11:20.150 --> 11:22.744
This place is wide open.
We could spot a surveillance unit.

11:22.950 --> 11:25.669
If Kavanaugh was planning a sting,
this wouldn't be the place.

11:25.870 --> 11:28.384
- He knows we would think that.
- We sniff out every inch.

11:28.590 --> 11:32.629
Triple-check every last detail.
We get one bad whiff, we bail.

11:33.710 --> 11:35.109
Hey, why don't you crank it up?

11:35.310 --> 11:38.029
Might still be some cops in Long Beach
who can't hear it.

11:38.710 --> 11:40.223
Why don't you relax, thief.

11:40.430 --> 11:42.864
I was hoping
I'd never see you in purple again.

11:43.070 --> 11:45.186
Never took it off.
You know how that goes.

11:45.390 --> 11:46.948
Yeah, I do.

11:47.710 --> 11:50.508
- This my boy Moses, man.
- Check them both.

11:50.710 --> 11:52.985
- Looking for this?
- No.

11:53.190 --> 11:54.908
We've had a little bug problem lately.

11:55.110 --> 11:58.022
- You think we work for the white law?
- White law, black power.

11:58.230 --> 12:01.222
It's all the same shit. Wanna make sure
our visit stays anonymous.

12:01.430 --> 12:03.307
- They're clean.
- No shit, Captain Cracker.

12:03.510 --> 12:06.980
That's clever. Can't understand
why the rap career didn't take off.

12:07.190 --> 12:10.307
Hey, hey, hey. Easy, easy, easy.

12:10.510 --> 12:13.502
- Now, what's your goddamn problem?
- Times change, man.

12:13.710 --> 12:15.780
I don't trust you,
or your ghost squad.

12:15.990 --> 12:18.299
Well, the lack of love is mutual.

12:18.510 --> 12:19.738
Yeah, I see that.

12:19.950 --> 12:22.384
You and Antwon.
Nothing like karma.

12:22.590 --> 12:24.148
Hey, the favour, I have to do.

12:24.350 --> 12:26.580
Taking mouth shit from M.C. Has-Been,
I don't.

12:26.790 --> 12:27.905
Come on, come on, fellas.

12:28.110 --> 12:32.581
Now, let's just put this history on hold
and get this shit done. Okay?

12:33.390 --> 12:36.188
- Let's go over it.
- Let's.

12:38.030 --> 12:39.543
Okay. There's one guard.

12:39.750 --> 12:42.184
Spends most of his shift
at the gatehouse, here.

12:42.390 --> 12:45.143
Guy of ours says
the warehouse is wall-to-wall cameras.

12:45.350 --> 12:48.467
They feed into monitors at the gate.
The seizure locker's here.

12:48.670 --> 12:52.458
Can't miss it. Right past the Hummer.
There's antiques, TVs and a safe.

12:52.670 --> 12:54.069
- A big one.
- Mitchell was right.

12:54.270 --> 12:57.262
We checked the inventory. Over
500 grand in watches and jewellery.

12:57.470 --> 12:58.949
Yeah, and that's all we go for.

12:59.150 --> 13:02.347
No one drives out of there
with a Hummer or a flat screen.

13:02.830 --> 13:04.149
- Yeah.
- Where are you?

13:04.350 --> 13:06.580
- Why?
- We need to talk.

13:08.310 --> 13:12.019
Kavanaugh's covering his bets in case
the case against you doesn't make.

13:12.230 --> 13:13.868
What do you mean "in case"?

13:14.070 --> 13:16.868
Surprised this clown
hasn't gotten the hook already.

13:17.070 --> 13:20.187
By acknowledging you failed to
clear the room when Terry was shot...

13:20.390 --> 13:23.666
...Kavanaugh's trying to characterise
your earlier statements as false.

13:23.870 --> 13:26.828
That's bullshit.
I've told the truth since day one.

13:27.030 --> 13:29.385
Nothing I said has changed
because the facts haven't.

13:29.590 --> 13:32.104
Well, then he's doing a good
job of twisting your words.

13:32.310 --> 13:35.143
It's not inconceivable
that he could cost you your retirement.

13:35.350 --> 13:36.419
Where did you hear that?

13:36.630 --> 13:40.100
Your case was referred
to the Police Committee for review.

13:41.230 --> 13:45.064
You let him try to take my pension.
PBA reps will have his head on a pike.

13:45.270 --> 13:46.908
Well, I wouldn't be so sure.

13:47.110 --> 13:50.307
You know, Kavanaugh could get this
as a way to end his investigation.

13:50.510 --> 13:53.661
Never mind prying a cop with
a sketchy jacket off the taxpayers' tit.

13:55.470 --> 13:58.382
Anyway, we said we'd share.
Thought you'd want the heads up.

13:58.590 --> 14:01.343
- Thanks.
- Hey, wait a minute.

14:01.550 --> 14:04.269
Is Kavanaugh making any noise
around here about me?

14:04.470 --> 14:07.701
- All's been quiet as it relates to you.
- Undermining him is a priority.

14:07.910 --> 14:09.662
For both of us.

14:15.590 --> 14:17.342
We'd like to speak to Alarico Trujillo.

14:17.550 --> 14:20.667
About a car accident he witnessed
a couple weeks back.

14:26.390 --> 14:28.540
We had a few more questions
about that accident.

14:28.750 --> 14:31.901
- I told you people everything.
- Didn't tell me about no car accident.

14:32.110 --> 14:33.259
I got nothing more to say.

14:33.470 --> 14:36.109
There's been another driver
that's been seriously injured.

14:36.310 --> 14:39.620
- It's important you come with us.
- Someplace private.

14:39.830 --> 14:41.183
Look, man...

14:42.230 --> 14:44.425
...just leave me alone, okay?

14:46.070 --> 14:48.743
We can do this another way
if we have to.

14:57.230 --> 15:00.063
Soon this is gonna be a lonely room
filled with empty lockers.

15:00.270 --> 15:03.626
You and me are the only ones on
the way out. I cut a deal with the DA.

15:07.230 --> 15:08.743
- What deal's that?
- Ask the chief.

15:08.950 --> 15:10.781
It's on his desk
waiting for a signature.

15:10.990 --> 15:14.062
He'll be out on parole before
the blood rushes back to your face.

15:15.790 --> 15:18.907
You don't mind if I check the facts
before I pack my bags, do you?

15:19.110 --> 15:20.543
I don't give a shit what you do.

15:30.350 --> 15:32.500
Yeah. Thanks.

15:33.390 --> 15:35.745
Chief's office hasn't even seen
Lemansky's deal yet.

15:35.950 --> 15:39.340
His mouthpiece is feeding him
a happy meal to keep his spirits up.

15:39.550 --> 15:44.908
Did Vic bite on that intel
about me going after his pension?

15:45.110 --> 15:47.340
You didn't see the steam
coming off his bald head?

15:47.550 --> 15:48.699
Beautiful, man.

15:48.910 --> 15:51.219
And I so want there to be trust
between you two.

15:54.190 --> 15:56.465
- I need to use your office.
- Of course.

15:56.670 --> 15:59.821
- Anything I can do for you?
- No. It's a police matter.

16:08.190 --> 16:11.182
Gave us all a scare,
that spill you took.

16:12.230 --> 16:16.701
Well, if you got one of these,
there's plenty of bounce to the ounce.

16:16.910 --> 16:17.979
Let me get to the point.

16:18.190 --> 16:20.704
I've been made aware
that you have a medical condition.

16:20.910 --> 16:23.140
One that could compromise
your ability to perform.

16:23.350 --> 16:26.581
You needed to disclose
a disease like lupus. You didn't.

16:26.790 --> 16:28.303
Because it was a personal matter.

16:28.510 --> 16:31.786
Suppose you took a header out in the
field. You could've put officers at risk.

16:31.990 --> 16:36.063
But it didn't happen. And I'm not here
because of how I knock down doors.

16:36.270 --> 16:39.103
I'm ordering you to see a physician
for a full medical review.

16:39.310 --> 16:41.346
Until then,
you're assigned to desk duty.

16:41.550 --> 16:45.020
Then let's get it done, ASAP.
I've got plenty of cases to clear.

16:45.230 --> 16:49.382
I'm responsible for the health
and welfare of everyone working here.

16:52.150 --> 16:53.708
Maybe you ought to do something...

16:53.910 --> 16:56.470
...about the bullshit in this place.
- Claudette, don't...

16:56.670 --> 17:00.788
Don't interrupt. This man, Kavanaugh,
that you've just given the place over to.

17:00.990 --> 17:03.140
